cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with saliency modeling using eye movement data and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with image and video analysis. The paper also proposes a novel saliency model based on generative adversarial network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses data augmentation techniques and their impact on saliency prediction, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning models for saliency prediction also falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on multiple datasets, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
